AWS Database services
----------------
Banking, Finance, Booking, ERP and CRM   --> Relational Database --> Amazon RDS and Amazon Aurora

Shopping Cart, Product Catalog , Custmoer Attributes --> Key Value or NoSQL Database  -> Amazon Dynamo DB

Content Management, User profiles -> Document database -> Amazon DocumentDB

Leaderboards, realtime analytics, caching and gaming -> In-memory database --> Amazon Elasticache

fraud detection, social networkinng and recomendation engine -> Graph database --> Amazon Neptune

Iot application and event tracking -> Timeseries database --> Amazon Timestream

Analytics , Data Marts -> Data Ware house --> Amazon Redshift

System of record, supply chain, health care, financial --> Ledger Databse --> Amazon Quantom Ledger Database (QLDB)

Genarative AI --> Vector database --> Amazon OpenSearch, Amazon RDS, Amazon Aurora, Amazon DocumentDB and Amazon Neptune


Amazon RDS features
---------------
Multi AZ deployment : 
standby DB is created in multiple AZs for high availability 
when data is written in primary db simultaneously the data is written in the stand by db
write is complete only when it is written in both (primary and standby) dbs
the standby DB is not accessible to users and applications until the there is failover in primary DB

Read replicas
Read replicas are the read only DBs created for scalability, decrease latency and also decrease load on primary db
can be created in same AZ, multiple AZ and diffrent region as well
